title.narrative: Relevant institutions of the central government and municipal governments have the capacities for the protection of children intheir migratory cycle.

description.narrative: With support from partners, UNICEF provided protection services to 42,324 children and adolescents on the move and 26,529 to parents and caregivers, through mental health, special protection and justice services, and supported their reintegration into their home communities. Of these, 12,194 were assisted at Returned Migrant Reception Centres, 2,742 at border points through humanitarian assistance during uncoordinated returns and 27,388 were assisted in communities. Services provided in the community benefitted 15,892 children and adolescents who received health and social services, 6,809 who received support through mental health services and 10,771 who received legal assistance.; | Status:Met | As-of Date:27/01/2022
